value.0: "Do you need any directions? If not, leave me to my patrol."
"Go to the HoloNet News Office. There's terminals in there that you may avail yourself of."

"You can head over to the Builder's Union. I don't trust the lot of them, rabble-rousers and seditionists, the lot, and they hate Czerka more than is healthy for them. But, they are also amongst some of the best fabricators in Veles."

"Try giving Orion's Armament a peek. They sometimes help with private R&D, and is even something of a competitor to Czerka. Generally quite helpful to new starfarers, and they will let you use the backroom."

"There's an order of mystics and foreigners, called the Jal Shey, who have opened up a shop at the main market's boulevard. They will let you use their backroom if you don't cause a fuss or break anything, and might even give you some tips when it comes to smithery."
"There's the General Store, of course. But if you want to sell them on the open market, just head to the Veles Market and use one of the market terminals. You'll find a lot more profit that way."

"From the center of Veles, where the plaza is, go southwards and turn right. It's all the way to the very end. Check the apartment terminals. You can buy an apartment there for yourself, and even furnish it with things you fabricate or you buy from others who can fabricate such furnishings."

"Right next to the Gates. The force-field there shouldn't stop you if you aren't designated as hostile, and the guards will let you through. You can make reports there, talk to bounty hunters, check bounties, or even try to sign up as a deputy."
"From the center of Veles, where the plaza is, go southwards and turn left. It's all the way to the very end."
"From the center of Veles, just keep going southwards. Can't miss the gate to the Viscaran wildlands."

"You can go to the General Store. There's all sort of equipment that you can buy there. From the center of Veles, where the plaza is, go southwards and turn left. It's one of the first buildings down the road."
"Where can I go to make HoloNet broadcasts?"
"Where can I go to learn and do fabrication?"
"Where can I go to learn and do engineering?"
"Where can I go to learn and do smithery?"
"Where can I go to sell things that I found?"
"Where can I buy an apartment for myself?"
"Can you direct me out of Veles?"
"Can you tell me where I can buy weapons, armors, and ammunition?"
